#T_SP=custom.Span|label
#Text=Top 3 Skills: Customer service iOS Developer support experience...
#Text=Communication skillsThe Mobile Developer will be responsible for design, development, and delivery of Ally native iOS mobile applications.
#Text=The candidate must exhibit strong interpersonal and communication skills.
#Text=The candidate must have experience interfacing with product owners as well as internal and external technical teams and resources.
#Text=Agile development experience is preferred.The role requires native mobile development experience with iOS universal applications and Apple watch.

#Text=Strong technical knowledge, coupled with indepth experience working with REST services, is required.The ideal candidate would have 3-5 years experience developing iOS native mobile applications.
#Text=Experience in a financial services environment is a plus.Primary responsibilities: Participate as a member of a mobile development scrum team.
#Text=Become a subject matter expert in the Ally mobile channel.
#Text=Partner with solution architects to leverage industry best practices to design and deliver high quality mobile applications.
#Text=Escalate issues to senior management early, before they create significant impact to a project/release.
#Text=Review and approve all mid-level design documentation.
#Text=Ensure that detail design documentation is competed, reviewed, and approved, as required.
#Text=Conduct or participate in code review sessions to ensure quality and performance.
#Text=Support the system integration and user acceptance testing resources.
#Text=Provide timely defect analysis, remediation, and reporting.
#Text=Review security testing reports/results and remediate potential vulnerabilities in a timely manner.

#Text=Stay abreast of emerging technologies or trends that could impact the mobile channel.Mandatory Skills: Design, develop and implement cohesive, highly-usable features and improvements to our existing native iOS applications.
#Text=Design and develop new native mobile applications, as required.
#Text=Experience with performance and memory tuning tools.
#Text=Experience in implementing unit tests.
#Text=Proficient understanding of code versioning tools such as GIT.
#Text=Strong knowledge of Objective-C, Swift, iOS SDK/Frameworks, REST APIs, JSON. 3+ years of experience designing and developing iOS native mobile applications.
#Text=Minimum one year experience working with SCRUM or Agile development environment is preferred.
#Text=Experience translating product requirements into design specifications.
#Text=Debugging and problem solving skills.
#Text=Understanding of MVC and MVVM development pattern.
#Text=Ensure quality software is delivered with minimal defects and no go live critical issues.
#Text=Knowledgeable of unit and automation testing tools Work directly with Architects and Product Managers to ensure quality solutions for all projects are being successfully delivered on time.
